o the process of recovering and restoring fourteen lost "HyperPoems" by the noted poet William Dickey; and finally, into the offices of Melcher Media, a small boutique design studio reimagining the future of the codex.A persistent theme is that bits—the ubiquitous ones and zeros of computing—are never self-identical, but always inflected by the material realities of particular systems, platforms, and protocols. These materialities are not liabilities: they are the very bulwark on which we stake the enterprise for preserving the future of literary heritage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBibliographyxHistoryy21st century. 0aBibliographyxMethodology. 0aDigital mediaxSocial aspects. 0aLiterature and technology. 0aLiteraturexResearchxMethodology. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aArchives.  aBibliography.  aBook history.  aBookmaking.  aBorn-digital.  aFuture of literary history.  aFuture of the archive.  aKamau Brathwaite.  aLiterary history.  aMedia archaeology.  aPublic memory.  aRosenbach lectures.  aShip of Theseus.  aToni Morrison.  aTransmedia.  aWilliam Dickey.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073921340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812298048423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812298048/original  a978-3-11-073921-3  University of Pennsylvania Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075